properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
Click up left "Browse" button on Tools palette first!
This will enable scripts to be in action.

Press right arrow key to proceed

properties.name: mouse Messages
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	put "mouseUp" into fld "output"
end mouseUp

on mouseDown
	put "mouseDown" into fld "output"
end mouseDown

properties.name: title
properties.text:
Try to press buttons to see message handling in action.
Check out the script inside button too!

properties.name: output
properties.text: mouseUp

properties.name: topic
properties.text: Mouse Event and Messages:

properties.script:
on openCard
	put "mouse event will be shown here..." into fld "output"
end openCard

properties.name: << Prev Card
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go prev
end mouseUp

properties.name: Next >>
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go next
end mouseUp

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text: Card Event and Messages:

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
Go to "Objects" menu, click it, and select
"Card Info..." menu item.

You will see card info dialog with "Script"
button. press it and see the card messages!

properties.name: output
properties.text:
clear... but you wont see this text in browse mode...
you can access this text from script in other card!

properties.script:
on openCard
	put "This text was generated in openCard message" into fld "output"
	put "Card specific initialization is good thing to do in this message" into line 2 of fld "output"
end openCard

on closeCard
	put "clear... but you wont see this text in browse mode..." into fld "output"
	put "you can access this text from script in other card!" into line 2 of fld "output"
end closeCard

on arrowKey dir
	put "you have pressed arrow key" + dir into fld "output"
    put "Click prev or next to move" into line 2 of fld "output"
end arrowKey

properties.name: go prev
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	go prev
end mouseUp

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text: Navigation Commands:

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
You can move between cards by

1. pressing arrowkey (if not captured by card)
2. "go" command
3. "push" and "pop" command (not working now)

pres "go prev" button to go back,
or press right arrow key to go next card

properties.name: put "hello"
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	put "hello"
end mouseUp

properties.name: put 42 into var1
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	put 42 into var1
    # later accessible by variable name var1
    # put var1 into fld "output"
end mouseUp

properties.name: put "message" into fld "output"
properties.script:
on mouseUp
    put "message from btn script" into fld "output"
end mouseUp

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text: Action Commands:

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
There are 3 ways of "put" action command.

1. put "hello"
    This will prompt message box with given text
2. put 42 into var1
    This will put a value into variable
3. put "message from script" into fld "output"
    This will put text into field

properties.script:
on openCard
    put "  " into fld "output"
end openCard

properties.name: enable PushMe
properties.script:
on mouseUp
	enable btn "PushMe"
end mouseUp

properties.name: disable PushMe
properties.script:

	disable btn "PushMe"
end mouseUp

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text: Action commands:

properties.name: <new field>
properties.text:
enable and disable command will
make button enabled or disabled

properties.text: Arithmetic Commands:

properties.text:
add, subtract, multiply, divide command
will perform its arithmetic .

properties.name: delayed output
properties.script:
on mouseUp
    wait 1 sec
    put "here you go!" into line 2 of fld "output"
end mouseUp

properties.text: Script Commands:

properties.text: wait command will stop script for given duration.
